    "domain": "medical",
    "domain_description": "The UKMLA Applied Knowledge Test assesses the knowledge, skills and professional behaviours required for safe practice as a newly qualified UK doctor. It evaluates clinical knowledge across all major specialties, emphasizing patient safety, evidence-based practice, clinical reasoning, and professional conduct. The exam integrates basic sciences with clinical application, covering presentation-based scenarios, investigation interpretation, management decisions, and ethical-legal considerations. Assessment focuses on common conditions, emergencies, and situations requiring immediate action, with emphasis on primary care and acute hospital settings.",
